The paper discusses a type system for ensuring correct memory management in lock-free data structures, which is a topic related to programming languages (cs.PL) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions read-copy-update (RCU) and hazard pointers, which are techniques used in operating systems (cs.OS) and concurrency (cs.LO). Finally, the paper discusses the safety of RCU linked list and binary search tree implementations, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE).
